    dc:description "FIGURE 68. Pachypygus gibber (Thorell, 1859), female. A, habitus, right; B, urosome, ventral; C, distal part of abdomen, right; D, distal part of abdomen, dorsal; E, distal part of abdomen, ventral; F, caudal ramus, lateral; G, rostrum; H, antennule; I, antenna; J, labrum. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, 0.5 mm; C–F, H–J, 0.01 mm; G, 0.02 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4591339/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591343>
    dc:description "FIGURE 69. Pachypygus gibber (Thorell, 1859), female. A, paragnath; B, mandible; C, maxillule; D, maxilla; E, maxilliped; F, leg 1; G, leg 2; H, leg 5. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4591343/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591345>
    dc:description "FIGURE 70. Pachypygus gibber (Thorell, 1859), female: A, leg 3; B, leg 4. Male: C, habitus, right; D, antennule; E, leg 3; F, leg 4; G, leg 5. Scale bars: A, B, 0.1 mm; C, 0.2 mm; D–G, 0.05 mm." ;
